  "chapter": {
    "number": 42,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Here Is My Servant"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "“Here is My Servant, whom I uphold,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "My Chosen One, in whom My soul delights.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "I will put My Spirit on Him,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and He will bring justice to the nations.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He will not cry out or raise His voice,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "nor make His voice heard in the streets.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A bruised reed He will not break",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and a smoldering wick He will not extinguish;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "He will faithfully bring forth justice.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He will not grow weak or discouraged",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2658
          },
          {
            "text": "before He has established justice on the earth.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "In His law the islands will put their hope.”",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2659
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "This is what God the LORD says—",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "He who created the heavens",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and stretched them out,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "who spread out the earth and its offspring,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "who gives breath to the people on it",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and life to those who walk in it:",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "“I, the LORD, have called you",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "for a righteous purpose,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and I will take hold of your hand.",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I will keep you and appoint you",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "to be a covenant for the people",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and a light to the nations,",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "to open the eyes of the blind,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "to bring prisoners out of the dungeon",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and those sitting in darkness",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "out from the prison house.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I am the LORD;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "that is My name!",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "I will not yield My glory to another",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "or My praise to idols.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Behold, the former things have happened,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and now I declare new things.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Before they spring forth",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I proclaim them to you.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "A New Song of Praise"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Sing to the LORD a new song—",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "His praise from the ends of the earth—",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "you who go down to the sea, and all that is in it,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "you islands,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2660
          },
          {
            "text": "and all who dwell in them.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Let the desert and its cities raise their voices;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "let the villages of Kedar cry aloud.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Let the people of Sela sing for joy;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "let them cry out from the mountaintops.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Let them give glory to the LORD",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and declare His praise in the islands.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The LORD goes forth like a mighty one;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "He stirs up His zeal like a warrior.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "He shouts; yes, He roars",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "in triumph over His enemies:",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "“I have kept silent from ages past;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I have remained quiet and restrained.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "But now I will groan like a woman in labor;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I will at once gasp and pant.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 15,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I will lay waste the mountains and hills",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and dry up all their vegetation.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "I will turn the rivers into dry land",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2661
          },
          {
            "text": "and drain the marshes.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 16,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I will lead the blind by a way they did not know;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I will guide them on unfamiliar paths.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "I will turn darkness into light before them",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and rough places into level ground.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "These things I will do for them,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and I will not forsake them.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 17,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "But those who trust in idols",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and say to molten images, ‘You are our gods!’",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "will be turned back in utter shame.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Israel Is Deaf and Blind"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 18,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Listen, you deaf ones;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "look, you blind ones, that you may see!",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 19,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Who is blind but My servant,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "or deaf like the messenger I am sending?",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Who is blind like My covenant partner,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "or blind like the servant of the LORD?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 20,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Though seeing many things, you do not keep watch.",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Though your ears are open, you do not hear.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 21,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The LORD was pleased, for the sake of His righteousness,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "to magnify His law and make it glorious.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 22,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "But this is a people plundered and looted,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "all trapped in caves or imprisoned in dungeons.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "They have become plunder with no one to rescue them,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and loot with no one to say, “Send them back!”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 23,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Who among you will pay attention to this?",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Who will listen and obey hereafter?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 24,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Who gave Jacob up for spoil,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and Israel to the plunderers?",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Was it not the LORD,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "against whom we have sinned?",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "They were unwilling to walk in His ways,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and they would not obey His law.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 25,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "So He poured out on them His furious anger",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the fierceness of battle.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "It enveloped them in flames,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but they did not understand;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "it consumed them,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but they did not take it to heart.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
